document_data.Usage:
* [[Rye bread]] was a dark, rich, and heavy bread that went well with [[beer]] and [[cheese]].{{Cite polyhedron/79/The Living City: The Painted Boat Restaurant|17}}
* Ring-shaped [[klarvel]] bread was made from rye.{{Cite web/Candlekeep Forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2010)/07-05 Ring-shaped Pastries}}
* [[Zurek]] was a kind of [[porridge]] made with rye flour.
* Rye was used to make [[whiskey]], as done by the [[Vast Brewing Company]].{{Cite polyhedron/92/The Living City: Vast Brewing Company|7}}
* The [[Burning Bronze Distillery]] in the City of Brass used an exclusive and rare kind of rye from the [[Prime Material plane]] to make their [[Burning Bronze Rye]] drink.{{Cite dragon/429/Bazaar of the Bizarre: Dine on the Wild Side|27}}
* The ''[[tools of the common man]]'' were marked by the imprint of blessed crops upon them. ''[[Gabe's shovel]]'' was blessed by a [[hawk]] dropping a grain of rye upon it.{{Cite polyhedron/142/Table Talk: Legendary Weapons|7}}
